-- Czechs Won’t Boost GDP With State Spending, Hospodarske Reports
-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2013-02-15T07:22:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-15/czechs-won-t-boost-gdp-with-state-spending-hospodarske-reports.html
The Czech government won’t boost
economic growth by increasing state spending,  Hospodarske Noviny 
reported, citing Finance Minister Miroslav Kalousek.  Economic prosperity can’t be based on short-term growth
financed by debt, the newspaper cited Kalousek as saying in an
interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
